# Security Review Checklist

Before submitting PRs, verify these security requirements:

## XSS Prevention

- [ ] No `innerHTML` with user-controlled data
- [ ] Using `textContent` for plain text rendering
- [ ] Using `createElement()` + `textContent` for structured content

```typescript
// VULNERABLE - never do this
element.innerHTML = `<span>${userInput}</span>`;

// SAFE
const span = document.createElement('span');
span.textContent = userInput;
element.appendChild(span);
```

## External Links

- [ ] All external links have `target="_blank"` AND `rel="noopener noreferrer"`

```astro
<!-- Correct -->
<a href="https://example.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Link</a>
```

## Secrets & Credentials

- [ ] No API keys, tokens, or secrets in code
- [ ] No `.env` files committed (use `.env.example` for templates)
- [ ] No hardcoded credentials or passwords

## Dependencies

- [ ] New dependencies are from trusted sources
- [ ] Checked for known vulnerabilities (`npm audit`)

## Content Collections

- [ ] User-submitted content is sanitized before rendering
- [ ] Schema validation catches malicious input patterns

## Headers (for deployment)

Verify `netlify.toml` security headers are present:

```toml
[[headers]]
  for = "/*"
  [headers.values]
    X-Frame-Options = "DENY"
    X-Content-Type-Options = "nosniff"
```
